---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Eyebrow from "../components/Eyebrow.astro";
import { site } from "../data/site";

const updated = "May 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms"
  description="The plain terms of using this site and working with a3b."
  noindex
>
  <section class="posthead">
    <div class="wrap wrap--narrow">
      <Eyebrow class="reveal">terms</Eyebrow>
      <h1 class="reveal" data-delay="1">Terms.</h1>
      <p class="lead reveal" data-delay="2">
        How this site may be used, and the plain shape of a working
        engagement. Specific projects are always confirmed in a written quote.
      </p>
      <div class="post-meta reveal" data-delay="2">
        <span class="pill">last updated {updated}</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="rule" />

  <section class="section-pad-sm">
    <div class="wrap wrap--narrow">
      <div class="prose reveal">
        <h2>Using this site</h2>
        <p>
          This website is published by a3b, a one-person video editing brand
          based in {site.location}. Its content — words, layout, the brand
          system — is owned by a3b. You are welcome to read, link to, and
          share it. Please do not copy it wholesale or pass the brand off as
          your own.
        </p>

        <h2>The work shown</h2>
        <p>
          While the public reel is being assembled, the pieces shown under
          Work are clearly marked archetypes — they describe how a3b
          approaches a kind of project, not delivered client work. Real,
          delivered pieces will replace them and will be labelled as such.
        </p>

        <h2>Enquiries and quotes</h2>
        <p>
          A brief request or email is an enquiry, not a contract. Nothing is
          booked until a written quote is sent and agreed. Prices listed on the
          site are starting points in Australian dollars; the figure that
          applies to your project is the one in your quote.
        </p>

        <h2>How an engagement works</h2>
        <p>
          Every engagement is confirmed in writing before work begins. The
          written quote sets out the deliverables, the price, the number of
          revision rounds, the schedule, and what is needed from you. The plain
          shape is consistent:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Work is priced per project, not per hour.</li>
          <li>
            Two rounds of revisions are included unless a quote says otherwise.
          </li>
          <li>
            You provide the footage and the inputs; a3b provides the edit,
            grade, sound, and finishing.
          </li>
          <li>
            Final files are delivered once the agreed fee is settled in full.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Ownership of finished work</h2>
        <p>
          On full payment, you own the finished films for the use described in
          your quote. a3b keeps the right to show the finished work as part of
          its own portfolio unless your quote agrees otherwise — useful, for
          example, where a project is confidential.
        </p>

        <h2>Fit</h2>
        <p>
          a3b only takes on work that fits the calm, considered aesthetic. If a
          project would be better served by a different approach, you will be
          told that directly rather than sold something that will not land.
        </p>

        <h2>Liability</h2>
        <p>
          a3b takes care with every engagement. To the extent the law allows,
          a3b is not liable for indirect or consequential loss, and any
          liability is limited to the fee paid for the work in question.
          Nothing in these terms removes rights you have under Australian
          Consumer Law.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          These terms may be updated; the date at the top changes when they
          are. The terms that apply to your project are the ones in force when
          your quote is agreed.
        </p>

        <hr />
        <p>
          <strong>A note before launch:</strong> this is a plain-language
          starting point, not legal advice. Have it reviewed by someone
          qualified in Australian law before the site goes live, and align it
          with the actual contract or quote template a3b uses.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
